title: Led Zeppelin - 1973.05.19 Fort Worth, Texas
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1973.05.19 Fort Worth, Texas   

Artist: Led Zeppelin
Date: 1973-05-19
Location: Fort Worth. TX
Venue: Tarrant County Convention Center
Source: Soundboard

Source: 
Incomplete excellent soundboard recording. 105 minutes.

Details: 
The recording is a very good balanced professional board tape.

Tracklist:
01. Intro
02. Rock And Roll
03. Celebration Day
04. Black Dog
05. Over The Hills And Far Away
06. Misty Mountain Hop
07. Since I've Been Loving You
08. No Quarter
09. The Song Remains The Same
10. The Rain Song
11. Dazed And Confused
12. Stairway To Heaven

Length: 105:00

Comments: 
Another great sounding show. The whole band sounds strong with some immense drumming from Bonham. Robert screeches and sounds strong and Jimmy and Jonesy steamroll through the set. Another shame the rest of the gig isn't available. During Black Dog the audience seemed to be quite dull so Plant commenting that: "What happened to you on the Ah! - Ah!? You were jerking off. What happened?" Also monitor problems truncated Since I've Been Loving You
